@startuml component-inheritance-overview
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

title Core Component Relationships and Reuse Boundaries

package "Card Domain" {
  class Card <<Control>> {
    +value : int
    +card_color : Color
    +original_index : int
    +interactive : bool
    +can_drag : bool
    --
    signal card_grabbed(card)
    signal card_dropped(card, drop_position)
  }

  class CardBuffer <<VBoxContainer>> {
    +slot_text : String
    +occupied_by : Card
    --
    signal card_placed_in_slot(card, slot)
    signal card_removed(card, slot)
  }

  class CardManager <<Control>> {
    +sorting validation
    +buffer/slot orchestration
    +completion checks
    +timer and move counting
  }

  class MultiplayerCardManager <<Control>> {
    +host-authoritative sync behavior
    +private buffer visibility rules
    +barrier synchronization (BarrierManager)
    +multiplayer state reconciliation
  }

  class BarrierManager <<RefCounted>> {
    +state : {RUNNING, WAITING, ACTIVE}
    +barrier_mode : int
    --
    signal barrier_state_changed
    signal thread_reached_barrier
    signal main_thread_assigned
  }

  CardManager <|-- MultiplayerCardManager : extends (path-based)
  CardManager "1" o-- "*" Card : manages
  CardManager "1" o-- "*" CardBuffer : orchestrates
  MultiplayerCardManager "1" *-- "1" BarrierManager : owns
}

package "Session/Connection Domain" {
  class ConnectionManager <<Node, Autoload>> {
    +lobby lifecycle state
    +player list updates
    +signal re-emission layer (inner Signals class)
  }

  class "GDSync (Autoload)" as GDSync {
    +call_func() / expose_func()
    +lobby_create() / lobby_join()
    +framework integration boundary
  }

  class SceneManager <<Node, Autoload>> {
    +goto_scene(res_path)
    +centralized scene transition
  }
}

MultiplayerCardManager --> GDSync : GDSync.call_func()\n(sync_card_moved, etc.)
ConnectionManager --> GDSync : subscribes to\nconnection/lobby signals
MultiplayerCardManager ..> ConnectionManager : reads host/client state
SceneManager <.. ConnectionManager : lobby scenes call\nSceneManager.goto_scene()

note right of MultiplayerCardManager
Extension-over-duplication strategy:
base rules remain in CardManager,
multiplayer concerns added in subclass
via path-based inheritance.
end note

@enduml

